  <data name="cboAuditMode.ToolTip" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Determines what data the audit collects:

• RightsOnly – Evaluate security roles and privileges only (fastest).
• RightsAndUsage – Also scan record ownership and activity (slower, more accurate).
• NoGraphRightsOnly – Rights only, skip Microsoft Graph license lookup.
• NoGraphRightsAndUsage – Rights + usage, skip Graph.

Modes with Graph require Tenant ID, Client ID, and Client Secret.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="lblSectionGraph.ToolTip" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Microsoft Graph API retrieves actual license assignments
from Entra ID for each Dataverse user.

Without Graph, the tool can still evaluate security roles
and usage patterns, but cannot determine which Microsoft 365
or Dynamics 365 licenses are actually assigned.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="txtClientId.ToolTip" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Application (Client) ID of your Azure App Registration.

Setup steps:
1. Azure Portal → App registrations → New registration
2. Add API Permissions (Application type, NOT Delegated):
   • Microsoft Graph → User.Read.All
   • Microsoft Graph → Directory.Read.All
   • Microsoft Graph → Organization.Read.All
3. Grant admin consent
4. Copy the Application (Client) ID here</value>
  </data>
  <data name="txtClientSecret.ToolTip" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Client Secret value from your App Registration.

Azure Portal → App registrations → Your app →
Certificates &amp; secrets → New client secret

Copy the Value (not the Secret ID).
Stored locally in the XrmToolBox settings file.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="chkUsageEnabled.ToolTip" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>When enabled, the tool queries Dataverse for:
• Record ownership per user (who owns business data?)
• Recent create/update activity per user

This significantly improves recommendation accuracy
but increases audit duration.</value>
  </data>
